			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A focus item is intended to allow the conjurer to &quot;concentrate&quot; harder on the casting of the pet, thus providing a higher quality pet.<BR>
<BR>
The Broom is for air pets, the shovel for earth pets, the stein for water pets and the torch for fire pets. <BR>
<BR>
The casting time for a pet is considerably longer using my torch (fire pet of course) and his size is NOTICEABLY bigger. As for his stats, not much on that yet, cause I'm 18, using lvl 16 pet spells. But at 20 Im hoping to really notice a difference.<BR>
<BR>
You must hold them in your primary slot while casting pet, after that you can remove them. They are no drop, so you can't even show anyone the stats on them. <BR>
<BR>
If you are adventurous, you can jump the boat in OOT when it passes the island Gornit is on. Send a shout if anyone has toes they don't want. <BR>
<BR>
I also saw the Cyclops toes for sale at a vendor somewhere, but for the life of me can't remember. Nek, or even Qeynos maybe.<BR>
<BR>
These items are a must have for accomplished mages, and a status symbol for twinkies. I have my torch at lvl 18, working on the others now. But from what I have seen, they are a must for bigger stronger pets, even around my level.<BR>
<BR>
Duroz - 18th Season Elementalist<BR>
Tholuxe Paells
